 BY BANYO TEMITAYO FORMER Vice Chairman of the Association of Nigerian Authors, Otunba Eddie Aderinokun, is dead. Aderinokun was said to have died on Sunday, January 3, 2021, at the age of 80, after a brief illness. A statement by his brother, Chief Kayode Aderinokun, on behalf of the family, confirmed his death. ”With great sadness, but with submission to the will of God, we announce the passing on to glory of our beloved Father, Grandfather, Husband, Brother, Otunba Eddie, Olayiwola Aderinokun, on the 3rd of January 2021, following a brief illness. Funeral arrangements will be announced by the Family,” the statement read. The late Aderinokun, a journalist and sports enthusiast, founded The Clusters, a pop group in Lagos in the late sixties, featuring great talents such as Berkeley Jones (guitarist), Tony Amadi, Linus Okechi and Jibade Thomas. He was an enigmatic and resourceful patron of the Committee for Relevant Arts (CORA) and its projects.  